Package: pantcl4r
Type: Package
Title: Literate programming using R, Python, Octave, Tcl, Graphviz and other tools
Version: 0.5.1
Date: 2024-11-19
Author: Detlef Groth, University of Potsdam, Germany
Maintainer: Detlef Groth <dgroth@uni-potsdam.de>
Description: Lightweight R package with no dependencies on non-standard R packages
    for literate programming using the pantcl application. 
    The package allows to embed programming code for different programming languages
    (R, Python, Octave, Tcl, Shell code etc), diagram code for tools like GraphViz,
    PLantUML or Dita and Mathematical equations into Markdown files and then convert
    the document into HTML.
Imports: tcltk
VignetteBuilder: pantcl4r                          
Suggests: pantcl4r
License: MIT + file LICENSE
NeedsCompilation: no
